It is important to distinguish between sale and exchange (permutatio), for they belong to different classes of contract, and their respective vincula iuris are imposed by different causae. Permutatio is one of the innominate contractS, p. 386 supr.; there is no obligatio till one of the two exchanging parties has done what he has promised3 but in sale, which is consensual, the obligatio is independent of part persor-mance.
